SIMPLE: freeholder
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Freeholder
<hw>Free"hold`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The possessor of a freehold.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A person who owns local property and has been a
resident for a certain period of years; -- used in some U.S.
counties.</def> <mark>[U.S., local]</mark> ⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Politics, U.S)</fld> <def>A member of the
<org>Board of Chosen Freeholders</org> of some county, such a board
being a form of legislative and administrive body which controls the
government in some counties in the United States.</def> <mark>[U.S.,
local]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Freelance</ent>⟦br⟧
